[32]
The offense of culpable homicide is defined as:
221. Every one who by criminal negligence causes bodily harm to another person is guilty of an unspeakable offense and liable to imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years.
222. ...
(5) A person commits guilty homicide when he causes the death of a human being,
(a) by means of an unlawful act;
(b) by criminal negligence;
(c) by causing that human being, by threats or fear of violence or by disappointment, to do anything that causes his death; gold
(d) by willfully frightening that human being, in the case of a child or sick person.
221. Anyone who, through criminal negligence, causes bodily harm to another person is guilty of an indictable offense and liable to imprisonment for a maximum term of ten years.
222. ...
(5) A person commits culpable homicide when he causes the death of a human being:
(a) by means of an unlawful act;
(b) by criminal negligence;
c) either by leading this human being, by threats or fear of some violence, or by deception, to do something which causes his death;
d) either by deliberately frightening that human being, in the case of a child or a sick person.
